{"lemma": "عامٌّ", "slug": "عامٌّ", "root": "ع.م.م", "root_slug": "ع-م-م", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-م-م", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "عامٌّ", "root": "عوم", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 9}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 8}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n30468", "n30633", "n31088", "n31275"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "general", "fa": "عمومی", "ur": "عام", "tr": "genel", "id": "umum", "bn": "সাধারণ", "es": "general", "fr": "général", "de": "allgemein", "ru": "общий", "zh": "普遍的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "year", "examples": [{"text": "وَلَقَدْ أَرْسَلْنَا نُوحًا إِلَى قَوْمِهِ فَلَبِثَ فِيهِمْ أَلْفَ سَنَةٍ إِلَّا خَمْسِينَ عَامًا فَأَخَذَهُمُ ٱلطُّوفَانُ وَهُمْ ظَالِمُونَ فَأَنْجَيْنَاهُ وَأَصْحَابَ ٱلسَّفِينَةِ وَجَعَلْنَاهَا آيَةً لِلْعَالَمِينَ", "english": "And We certainly sent Noah to his people, and he remained among them nine hundred and fifty years, and the flood seized them while they were wrongdoers. But We saved him and the companions of the ship, and We made it a sign for the worlds."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a period of twelve lunar months; lunar year"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "public"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "prevalent, universal"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "general", "examples": [{"text": "بلغت نسبة التصويت العامة في إسرائيل حتى الساعة الثامنة 62% وهي اقل 2.6% عن عام 2015.", "english": "Voter turnout for the general population of Israel as of 8:00 reached 62%, which is 2.6% less than in the year 2015."}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "common, ordinary"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to float"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to swim"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Since this word competes with سَنَة (sana), عَام (ʕām) is suggested to be loaned from Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩣 (ʿm /⁠*ʿām⁠/, “year”). Compare Ge'ez ዓም (ʿam, “year”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of عَمَّ (ʕamma, “to be general, to be common, to prevail”) (cognate to Hebrew עַם (am, “nation”) and עֲמָמִי ('amamí, “public”)). Contamination from Parthian 𐫍𐫀𐫖 (hʾm /⁠hām-⁠/, “same”) or its Middle Iranian analogues such as engendering Old Armenian համ- (ham-, “same, homo-; whole, pan-”) is considered."}, "ipa": ["/ʕaːm/", "/ʕaːmm/", "/ʕaː.ma/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n30468", "headword_ar": "عَامٌّ", "root": "Em", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "part. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eam~a", "text_ar": "عَمَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; applied to rain &c. [as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Common,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "general,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "universal;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generally,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "universally, comprehensive:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: see 1, first sentence:"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaAS~N", "text_ar": "خَاصٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEaAm~apu", "text_ar": "العَامَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b3-  Also [A"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "general"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "word; i. e.] a word"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "applied by a single application to many things, not restricted, including everything to which it is applicable:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the words “ by a single application ” exclude the homonym, because this is by several applications; and the saying “ to many things ” excludes what is not applied to many things, as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodN", "text_ar": "زَيْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamorNw", "text_ar": "عَمْرٌو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and the words “ not restricted ” exclude the nouns of number, for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmiAy^ipu", "text_ar": "المِايِةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for instance, is applied by a single application to many things and includes everything to which it is applicable, but the many things are restricted: and the words “ including everything to which it is applicable ” exclude the indeterminate plural, as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotu rijaAlFA", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُ رِجَالًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", all men not being seen: and the word is either"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm~", "text_ar": "عامّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "by its form and its meaning, as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~ijaAlu", "text_ar": "الرِّجَالُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm~", "text_ar": "عامّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "by its meaning only, as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~ahoTu", "text_ar": "الرَّهْطُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alqawomu", "text_ar": "القَوْمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (KT. [The word in this sense is often used in the lexicons, but is expl. in few of them, as being conventional and post-classical.])"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30633", "headword_ar": "عَامٍ", "root": "EmY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "One"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who does not see his road,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "way."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAmiyapN", "text_ar": "عَامِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", applied to a land ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroDN", "text_ar": "اَرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEomaY", "text_ar": "اَعْمَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b3-  Also, [thus applied,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Of which the traces are becoming"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "become"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "effaced,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obliterated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEomaA='N", "text_ar": "اَعْمَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in three places. ―         -b5-  Applied to a woman, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAmiyapN", "text_ar": "عَامِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bak~aA='apN", "text_ar": "بَكَّا=ءَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) [a strange epithet,] meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Having very little milk."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TK.)       -A2-  Applied to a man,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAmK", "text_ar": "عَامٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAmK", "text_ar": "رَامٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Casting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n31088", "headword_ar": "عَامٌ", "root": "Ewm", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A year"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanapN", "text_ar": "سَنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, K;) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HawolN", "text_ar": "حَوْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; [not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanapN", "text_ar": "سَنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for] El. Jawáleekee says, the common people do not distinguish between the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snh", "text_ar": "سنه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", making them both to have the same meaning; but the right state of the case is what I have been told on the authority of Ahmad Ibn-Yahyà [i. e. Th], that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snh", "text_ar": "سنه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is from any day from which one commences a reckoning to the like thereof, and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is only ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a period of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a winter and a summer;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and it is also said in the T and in the Bári that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawol", "text_ar": "حَوْل"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that makes an end of a winter and a summer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so that every"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snp", "text_ar": "سنة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but every"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snp", "text_ar": "سنة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is not an"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for when you reckon from a day to the like thereof, that is a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snp", "text_ar": "سنة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and there may be in it half of the summer. and half of the winter, whereas the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is only"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a winter and a summer, without interruption:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, MF: *) Er-Rághib mentions a difference in the uses of the words"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAmN", "text_ar": "عَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanapN", "text_ar": "سَنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as has been stated in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snw", "text_ar": "سنو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snY", "text_ar": "سنى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanapN", "text_ar": "سَنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in that art.] and Suh says, in the R, that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "snp", "text_ar": "سنة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is longer than the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; that the former is “ a single revolution of the sun; ” and that the latter is applied to the ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "twelve"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Arabian months"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "collectively"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: it is said to be called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EAm", "text_ar": "عام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of the sun's"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eawom", "text_ar": "عَوْم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or coursing] through all of its zodiacal signs [during the period which it denotes]: (TA:) its pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEowAmN", "text_ar": "اَعْوامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) because the sing. is originally of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEalN", "text_ar": "فَعَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawamN", "text_ar": "عَوَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Msb:) it has no other pl. than this. (TA.) ―         -b2-  One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lqiytuhu", "text_ar": "لقِيتُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAmFA A^aw~ala", "text_ar": "عَامًا اَوَّلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I met him in a former year;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "generally meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the year immediately preceding,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or, as we say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "last year"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; making the last word imperfectly decl. as being an epithet [and of the measure of a verb]: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqituhu EaAmFA A^aw~alFA", "text_ar": "لَقِتُهُ عَامًا اَوَّلًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I met him in a year before:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "generally meaning the same as the phrase preceding]; making the last word perfectly decl. as not being an epithet [but an adv.n. and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wA^l", "text_ar": "وال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") or the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a year"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "before this year;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "even if it be by a number of years: ('Alee El-Kári, on the authority of Seer, in a marginal note in my MS. copy of the K, art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Awl", "text_ar": "اول"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) and one says also, accord. to AZ and IAar,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqaytuhu EaAma AlA^aw~ali", "text_ar": "لَقَيتُهُ عَامَ الاَوَّلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wA^l", "text_ar": "وال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";) or the is rarely said; (K and TA in that art.;) or should not be said; (ISk, S and TA in that art.;) nor should one say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqaytuhu EaAma A^aw~ala", "text_ar": "لَقَيتُهُ عَامَ اَوَّلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISk TA in the present art.) And [in like manner] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA raA^ayotuhu mu*o EaAmN A^aw~alu", "text_ar": "ما رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْ عَامٌ اَوَّلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", putting the last word in the nom case as being an epithet, (S and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wA^l", "text_ar": "وال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) as though he said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aw~alu mino EaAminaA", "text_ar": "اَوَّلُ مِنْ عَامِنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have not seen him since a year preceding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one year"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S in that art.;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu*o EaAmN A^aw~ala", "text_ar": "مُذْ عَامٌ اَوَّلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", putting the last word in the accus. case as an adv n., (S and K * in that art.,) as though he said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu*o EAmN qabola EaAminaA", "text_ar": "مُذْ عامٌ قَبْلَ عَامِنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "since a year before"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "our year"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S in that art.;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu*oEaAmFA A^aw~ala", "text_ar": "مُذْعَامًا اَوَّلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu*o EaAmu AlA^aw~ali", "text_ar": "مُذْ عَامُ الاَوَّلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are also mentioned by different authors (L in art,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mn*", "text_ar": "منذ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") And [using the dim. form] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqituhu *aAta", "text_ar": "لَقِتُهُ ذَاتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEuwayomi", "text_ar": "العُوَيْمِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I met him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the course of some years;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like as one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytuhu *aAta Alz~umayoni", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُهُ ذَاتَ الزُّمَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aAta mar~apK", "text_ar": "ذَاتَ مَرَّةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) or the meaning is, ("}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "some few years ago;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "three years ago"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "more,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ten:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, Az, TA:) and it is like the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytuhu muno*u", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُهُ مُنْذُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sunay~aAtK", "text_ar": "سُنَيَّاتٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the fem. form is used because they mean by it"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mar~ap waAHidap", "text_ar": "مَرَّة وَاحِدَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Az, TA.) ―         -b3-  One says also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAqapN baAzilu EaAmK", "text_ar": "نَاقَةٌ بَازِلُ عَامٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAzilu EaAmihaA", "text_ar": "بَازِلُ عَامِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A she-camel that has passed a year,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "her year, after cutting her tush"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAzil EaAmayoni", "text_ar": "بازِل عَامَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that has passed two years after cutting the tush."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MF and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bzl", "text_ar": "بزل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAmapN", "text_ar": "عَامَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places.       -A3-  It is also said in the K that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEaAmu", "text_ar": "العَامُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~ahaAru", "text_ar": "النَّهَارُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but this is a mistake and a mistranscription it is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEayaAmu", "text_ar": "العَيَامُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and its place is art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eym", "text_ar": "عيم"}, {"kind": "text", 